Here's a cheatsheet for you:
Are there dishes in the sink? Clean them
Is there dirt/pet hair on the floor? Vacuum
Clothes in the hamper(s)? Do the laundry
Items where they don't belong? Put it away
Windows smudged? Wipe them
Are there cobwebs? Dust
Counters cluttered? Clear them

Spouses, just look around and pick something. Don't leave it to your partner to tell you what needs done. You're not taking more off your partners plate then, you're just replacing it with delegation.

This agreement makes me think of pro-lifers really. Stop worrying about the fetus and worry about what happens after. If the parents are loving and supportive after birth then why does it matter if they have a gender reveal during pregnancy (again, provided it's safe)?

I think gender reveal parties are fine if you do them safely - for example I used food coloring in water. It should be harmless fun and in no way determines how a family will treat them if later they come out as trans.

In general, most smokers I've been around have all been friendly and will answer any questions you have, so ask. Unrealistic scenes in a story can very easily make a reader pause while good realistic descriptions can draw a reader in.
~ happy writing ~

- (in my experience) pot makes you a bit of a hypochondriac- it's a d*co move to mention cotton mouth to a high person
- you can get the munchies but not always, again it depends on the strain
- it can help you hyper fixate on a project (getting lost in a painting for example)

Going back to pot:
- there are multiple strands
- some strands make you relaxed and others give you energy
- smoking/eating A LOT can alter your vision but not make you hallucinate 
- can be smoked in making ways and provide different strength with certain methods

- to try lowering their voice because they were teased growing up about their voice being high pitched
- because they picked it up for one of the dumb reasons above and then were addicted

- to give them extra (or any) breaks at work
- likewise to give them a reason to step outside or away from people or a stressful event

Some reasons people smoke:
- yes, because they think it makes them look cool
- because they hate themselves (literally)
- as a stress reliever
- to be social with friends that smoke
- because a family member did while growing up and now the smell reminds them of that person

containers, salsa jars, etc) or they just smoke outside
- cigarettes butts take a long time to decompose (if ever) - there will be some found in grass or bushes

- grey smudges on books, counters, etc from brushing ash off and smearing it
- not every smoker has a deep voice
- not every smoker can do smoke tricks (easier to do with a vape or hookah anyway)
- not every smoker has an ash tray (some use trash instead - think empty coffee-

Other signs of a smoker:
- yellowed skin around the fingers they smoke from (in my experience smokers have a preferred hand, position, and way they sweep the cigarette to their mouth)
- 1 or 2 holes in clothing from an ember falling or them dropping the cig
